Heat the oil in a large lidded saucepan over a medium-low heat. Add the chorizo and cook until the oil starts to run from the chorizo.Add the onion and garlic and cover with the lid. Cook, stirring from time to time, until soft.Add the tomatoes and beans, stir well and cover, simmer for 10 minutes. Add a little water if the stew is too thick.Add the parsley, season to taste with salt and pepper and stir well.Serve in soup bowls, with crusty bread.